Section 3: Placeholder for Future Dependencies
-----------------------------------------------

This section will be populated as BalanceFrame adds external dependencies.

Instructions for updating this file:

1. When adding a new direct or transitive dependency:
   a. Determine the dependency's license from its repository or package metadata.
   b. Add a new numbered section above this placeholder describing:
      - Project name and version
      - Repository URL
      - License name and link to the full license text
      - Relationship to BalanceFrame (bundled, referenced via API, inspiration only, etc.)
      - Full license text or a reference to where it is included in this repository
   c. If the dependency is bundled into a distributed artifact, move it above
      the placeholder and note its scope and any applicable copyright notices.

2. This file MUST be updated before merging any PR that introduces a new
   external dependency, whether direct or transitive, source or binary.

3. Dependencies that are development-only (dev dependencies, test fixtures)
   and are NOT distributed in release artifacts SHOULD still be documented
   for transparency unless they are entirely internal to the build process.

4. Review this file before each release to ensure all bundled dependencies
   are accurately represented.

